Chief of Staff Senior Program Manager

initiatives.name: SOCOM Phase 2 Autonomous ISR Production
initiatives.description: Full-rate production and delivery of Ghost autonomous ISR platforms under SOCOM Phase 2 contract. Includes integration of upgraded sensor payloads, Lattice OS v4.x connectivity, and field support packages for deployed units. Deliverables span 24 aircraft systems with associated ground control stations and training materials.

initiatives.name: Counter-UAS Next Gen Development
initiatives.description: Development of next-generation Anvil counter-drone interceptor system with improved autonomous engagement capabilities for US Army PEO Missiles & Space. Focus areas include extended range engagement envelope, multi-target tracking, and integration with Army IBCS command network. Currently in CDR phase with first article testing planned for Q1 2026.

initiatives.name: UK MoD Autonomous Systems Partnership
initiatives.description: Establish production capability and delivery pipeline for autonomous surveillance systems under the UK Ministry of Defence partnership contract. Includes technology transfer planning, UK security accreditation, and establishment of in-country support capabilities through the London program office. First capability demonstration milestone targeted for Q4 2025.

initiatives.name: Dive-LD Undersea Production Block 2
initiatives.description: Final production block delivery of Dive-LD autonomous undersea vehicles for NAVWAR. Program achieved full delivery and customer acceptance of 12 vehicles with integrated sonar packages. Sustainment transition documentation completed. Program closed out with all deliverables accepted.

initiatives.name: DSTL Counter-UAS Integration Package
initiatives.description: Integration and sustainment of Anvil counter-UAS systems for UK DSTL evaluation program. Includes modification of Anvil system software for UK-specific threat profiles, installation of UK communications interfaces, and provision of technical data packages for DSTL test and evaluation teams.

initiatives.name: Army Futures Rapid Counter-Drone Deployment
initiatives.description: Rapid fielding of counter-drone capability packages to Army Futures Command test units. Includes expedited production of four mobile Anvil systems, training of operator cadre, and collection of field performance data for next-gen requirements refinement.

initiatives.name: General Dynamics CUAS Subsystem Integration
initiatives.description: Provide Anvil counter-UAS subsystem components to General Dynamics Mission Systems for integration into their layered air defense architecture. Deliverables include interface control documents, hardware kits, and integration support engineering.

initiatives.name: NATO NCIA Counter-Drone Licensing Program
initiatives.description: Platform licensing and technical data delivery for NATO member adoption of counter-UAS capabilities. Program on hold pending resolution of NATO security accreditation requirements. NCIA reviewing Anduril's proposed data handling procedures for classified technical data.

initiatives.name: MDA Anvil Sustainment Services
initiatives.description: Long-term sustainment and field support for deployed Anvil systems under Missile Defense Agency programs. Includes depot-level maintenance, software updates, spare parts provisioning, and 24/7 field service representative coverage at three operational sites.

initiatives.name: Ghost Platform Operational Support — Agency Program
initiatives.description: Ongoing operational support and platform maintenance for Ghost autonomous ISR systems deployed under a classified agency program. Services include mission planning support, platform health monitoring, sensor calibration, and rapid deployment response capability.

initiatives.name: AFLCMC Tactical ISR Data Services
initiatives.description: Delivery of ISR data processing and exploitation services under Air Force AFLCMC sustainment contract. At-risk status driven by platform reliability issues in deployed Altius systems affecting data collection rates. Team working with hardware engineering on firmware fix targeting 95% availability.

initiatives.name: BAE Systems ISR Collaboration Study
initiatives.description: Joint study with BAE Systems on next-generation ISR data fusion architectures. Exploring integration of Anduril sensor data with BAE's electronic warfare systems for enhanced situational awareness. Includes proof-of-concept demonstration and joint technical paper.

initiatives.name: Agency Tactical ISR Support Services
initiatives.description: Tactical ISR data processing and analysis support for a DoD agency customer. Services include real-time sensor feed management, target track correlation, and intelligence product generation supporting operational planning cycles.

initiatives.name: L3Harris Multi-Domain C2 Integration Pilot
initiatives.description: Pilot program to demonstrate Lattice OS integration with L3Harris tactical communications systems for multi-domain command and control. Includes protocol adaptation layer development, joint interoperability testing, and demonstration at next Joint Warfighting Assessment exercise.

initiatives.name: Lattice Platform Sustainment & Operator Training
initiatives.description: Enterprise sustainment and operator training program for Lattice OS deployments across multiple DoD customer environments. Includes platform patches, security updates, classroom and virtual training delivery, and 24/7 help desk support for 200+ active operator accounts.

initiatives.name: SOCOM Joint C2 Lattice Deployment
initiatives.description: Enterprise deployment of Lattice OS command and control platform across SOCOM operational units. Program on hold pending SOCOM review of deployment architecture following network security assessment findings. Technical team preparing remediation package for identified items.

initiatives.name: AFLCMC Lattice OS Enterprise Integration
initiatives.description: Large-scale integration of Lattice OS into Air Force enterprise C2 infrastructure under AFLCMC contract. At-risk due to platform API performance issues under multi-tenant load — current P99 response time at 265ms vs. 200ms requirement. Engineering working API layer refactor targeting compliance by Q4.

initiatives.name: Undersea Distributed Sensor Network — Phase 2
initiatives.description: Development and deployment of distributed undersea sensor network nodes for maritime domain awareness. Phase 2 expands network from 8 to 24 nodes with enhanced acoustic processing and satellite uplink capability. Includes node manufacturing, ocean installation, and shore-side data center integration.

initiatives.name: Maritime Sensor Sustainment — Critical Infrastructure
initiatives.description: Ongoing sustainment of deployed maritime autonomous sensor systems supporting critical infrastructure monitoring missions. Services include preventive maintenance cycles, corrosion management, sensor recalibration, and data pipeline health monitoring for continuous maritime surveillance operations.

initiatives.name: Five Eyes ISR Data Sharing Platform
initiatives.description: Development and deployment of a secure ISR data sharing platform enabling intelligence product exchange among Five Eyes partner nations. Includes cross-domain security architecture, data format standardization, and establishment of operational procedures for multinational ISR collaboration.

initiatives.name: UK DSTL ISR Platform Evaluation
initiatives.description: Technical evaluation program with UK DSTL to assess Anduril ISR platform capabilities for potential UK procurement. Includes platform demonstrations, technical data exchange, and collaborative threat scenario testing. Deliverable: technical evaluation report and procurement recommendation.

initiatives.name: UK MoD ISR Integration Study
initiatives.description: Feasibility study for integrating Anduril ISR capabilities into UK MoD operational architecture. Covers network integration requirements, UK security accreditation pathway, and in-country support model definition. Supporting the broader UK MoD Autonomous Systems Partnership.

initiatives.name: Forest Service Autonomous Monitoring R&D
initiatives.description: Applied AI research contract developing autonomous wildfire detection and monitoring capabilities using adapted ISR sensor platforms. Includes computer vision algorithm development for smoke and fire detection, integration with National Interagency Fire Center systems, and field trials in western US forests.

initiatives.name: Rapid Prototyping — Next-Gen Effector Concepts
initiatives.description: Rapid prototyping of advanced effector concepts under DoD innovation pathway. Fast-cycle design-build-test program exploring novel approaches to small autonomous systems for contested environments. Three design cycles planned with progressive capability demonstrations.

initiatives.name: Applied AI Autonomy Research — Swarm Coordination
initiatives.description: Applied research in multi-agent autonomous coordination algorithms for contested RF environments. Developing decentralized decision-making protocols that maintain swarm coherence without continuous communications. Includes simulation environment development and hardware-in-the-loop testing.

initiatives.name: Army PEO Advanced Interceptor Study
initiatives.description: Advanced concept study for next-generation kinetic interceptor designs for Army PEO Missiles & Space. Exploring novel guidance approaches and propulsion configurations for enhanced performance against evolving aerial threats. Trade study phase with down-select to two concepts for detailed analysis.

initiatives.name: Applied AI Research — Sensor Fusion Algorithms
initiatives.description: Development of advanced multi-modal sensor fusion algorithms for autonomous target identification and tracking. Research covers electro-optical, infrared, radar, and acoustic sensor data integration using transformer-based architectures. Targeting 30% improvement in classification accuracy over current baseline.

initiatives.name: Booz Allen Advanced Analytics Collaboration
initiatives.description: Collaborative study with Booz Allen Hamilton on advanced data analytics methodologies for defense intelligence applications. Exploring integration of Anduril's Lattice data processing capabilities with Booz Allen's analytical frameworks for enhanced pattern-of-life analysis.

initiatives.name: Arsenal-1 Production Scale-Up
initiatives.description: Validate and certify the Arsenal-1 manufacturing facility in Columbus, OH for full-rate production of autonomous systems. Includes production line qualification, quality management system certification, equipment installation and calibration, and first article inspection for three platform variants. Target: achieve Milestone C production readiness by Q4 2025. Currently 6 months behind original schedule due to contractor availability and equipment installation sequencing.

initiatives.name: SOCOM Phase 3 Capture Campaign
initiatives.description: Cross-functional capture campaign to win the SOCOM Phase 3 Autonomous ISR program, estimated at $500M over 5 years. Activities include solution architecture development, teaming arrangements, customer engagement, proposal preparation, and competitive intelligence. Proposal submission targeted for December 2025.

initiatives.name: AUKUS Program Expansion
initiatives.description: Expand Anduril's presence in the AUKUS partnership through establishment of program offices in Sydney and London, pursuit of bilateral technology sharing agreements, and development of Australia-specific manufacturing partnerships. Includes regulatory compliance for ITAR and Australian DSGL requirements.

initiatives.name: Lattice OS NATO Certification
initiatives.description: Achieve NATO interoperability certification for Lattice OS platform to enable deployment across allied nation C2 architectures. Includes STANAG compliance testing, NATO security accreditation, multi-tenant performance optimization (P99 <200ms target), and documentation package preparation. Currently at-risk due to API performance gap.

initiatives.name: IPO Readiness Program
initiatives.description: Prepare Anduril for potential 2026 IPO through financial systems hardening, SOX compliance preparation, board governance formalization, and investor relations infrastructure buildout. CFO-led with support from external advisors. Maintaining optionality — not a commitment to go public, but ensuring readiness if the board decides to proceed.

initiatives.name: CMMC Level 3 Compliance
initiatives.description: Achieve Cybersecurity Maturity Model Certification Level 3 across all Anduril facilities handling CUI. Includes gap assessment remediation, implementation of 130 security practices, evidence collection, and preparation for third-party assessment. Columbus SCIF buildout is a dependency. Assessment targeted for Q4 2025.

initiatives.name: Engineering Process Standardization
initiatives.description: Establish standardized program delivery processes across engineering and program management to bridge Silicon Valley development practices with defense compliance requirements. Includes milestone review templates, technical documentation standards, earned value management implementation, and cross-functional workflow definition. Led by VP Program Management in collaboration with engineering leadership.

initiatives.name: Workday Platform Migration
initiatives.description: Migration from legacy HR and financial management systems to Workday unified HCM platform. Completed: data migration, user acceptance testing, parallel run, and go-live. All employee records, benefits administration, and basic financial reporting now on Workday. Phase 2 (advanced analytics modules) planned for FY26.

initiatives.name: Columbus SCIF Buildout
initiatives.description: Construction and accreditation of a Sensitive Compartmented Information Facility at the Columbus, OH Arsenal-1 campus. Required for classified program work at the manufacturing site. Includes physical construction, ICD 705 compliance, network installation, and SCIF accreditation. Dependency for CMMC Level 3 certification.
